column3: Retrieve IP address and other network configuration items for your PC
Access to the myMiami application from your web browser
myMiami uses CAS to verify authentication; redirects your web browser to the CAS server for authentication.  The diagram is a simplification of this exchange.
CAS uses our directory services (Active Directory or OpenLDAP) to verify usernames and passwords
Acctgen feeds information about users to myMiami
Acctgen feeds information about users to Active Directory and OpenLDAP
Acctgen feeds user, course, and enrollment information to Niihka
Banner provides user, course, and enrollment information, etc. to acctgen to distribute to other systems.
Banner provides user, course, and enrollment information to DARS
Niihka uses CAS to verify authentication; redirects to CAS server if no authentication has been established.
Niihka final grade information can be sent to Banner at the end of a term.
myMiami retrieves Niihka course availability and enrollment information for use in the myCourses module
myMiami provides links to Chalk & Wire
Niihka provides links to Chalk & Wire
Niihka provides single-signon integration with WebEx
Niihka provides access to the TurnItIn service
Niihka provides access to the TurningPoint service (clickers)
